## Platform-Specific Change Rules

This app runs on three platforms: iOS, Android, and Web.

RULE 1 — NEVER break other platforms
When fixing a bug on one platform, you must not
change anything that affects the other two platforms.
If a fix requires a change that touches shared code,
STOP and tell the user before doing anything.

RULE 2 — How to make platform-specific fixes
Use Capacitor.getPlatform() to detect the platform
at runtime. Example:

import { Capacitor } from '@capacitor/core'
const isIOS = Capacitor.getPlatform() === 'ios'
const isAndroid = Capacitor.getPlatform() === 'android'
const isWeb = Capacitor.getPlatform() === 'web'

Apply styles or logic conditionally using these flags.
Never use CSS overrides that affect all platforms
just to fix one.

RULE 3 — Before touching shared files
If a fix requires editing any of these files,
STOP and ask the user for permission first:
- index.html
- App.tsx
- AppLayout.tsx
- theme.css
- main.tsx

These files affect ALL platforms simultaneously.
Explain what you want to change and why before touching them.

RULE 4 — Safe places to make platform fixes
Platform-specific fixes should go in the individual
screen file only, using the Capacitor.getPlatform()
check, not in shared layout files.
